    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="How to Scan in C4 PTR" class="article-title">
          How to Scan in C4 PTR
          
        </h1>

        <div class="article-author">
          
          <div class="article-meta">
            

            <div class="meta-group">
              
                <span class="meta-data"><time datetime="2026-06-03T14:43:11Z" title="2026-06-03T14:43:11Z" data-datetime="relative">June 03, 2026 14:43</time></span>
                <span class="meta-data">Updated</span>
              
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        
          <div class="article-subscribe"><div data-helper="subscribe" data-json="{&quot;item&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/hc/en-us/articles/52275761937555-How-to-Scan-in-C4-PTR/subscription.json&quot;,&quot;follow_label&quot;:&quot;Follow&quot;,&quot;unfollow_label&quot;:&quot;Unfollow&quot;,&quot;following_label&quot;:&quot;Following&quot;,&quot;can_subscribe&quot;:true,&quot;is_subscribed&quot;:false}"></div></div>
        
      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><p>Scanning allows your fleet to search space for <strong>SDUs</strong>, which can be used in crafting recipes.</p><p>This guide explains how to prepare a scanning fleet, move it to the area you want to scan, and start a scan sweep.</p><blockquote><p><strong>Note:</strong> C4 PTR is still in development. Scanning behavior, scan patterns, costs, and results may change over time.</p></blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6Y1N2DMY5PCXK0Z10WV0G0">Before you start</h2><p>Before scanning, you need to create a fleet and move it to the area where you want to scan.</p><p>If you need help with those steps, check these guides first:</p><ul>
<li class="wysiwyg-list-bold" data-list-item-id="e7edc7acc477866eab8a904e813c4fbc6"><a href="/hc/en-us/articles/52251721868563"><strong>How to Create and Use a Fleet in C4 PTR</strong></a></li>
<li class="wysiwyg-list-bold" data-list-item-id="ef61699611d41f0988f70ae4468639a79"><a href="/hc/en-us/articles/52273962138771"><strong>How to Move a Fleet in C4 PTR</strong></a></li>
</ul><p>To scan, your fleet needs:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="e484725e12fec48a415945138128c41a9">
<strong>Fuel</strong> to move</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e086c2d26341682cafbdc1888677e1775">
<strong>Repair Kits</strong> to perform scan sweeps</li>
</ul><p>Make sure your fleet has both before you start.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6Y2NK1D169VH2AJ4TFJMCE">Step 1: Prepare your fleet</h2><p>Before starting a scan:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="e0b1d620d15f5856afe4083ad14f91b3c">Create your fleet.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ee97464519859ded9f44819cb2a4a47f5">Add the ships you want to use.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e55d60546f4333582babd3cc95d99da09">Add enough <strong>Fuel</strong> for travel.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e274044787ec46626a7f834e54dd69c5f">Add enough <strong>Repair Kits</strong> for scanning.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e93b96d204045676b0f384306530fda14">Undock the fleet.</li>
</ol><p>Your fleet must be <strong>undocked</strong> before it can scan.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 3147/1799;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52275761921811" width="3147" height="1799"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6YT82R470RS7EAW4HQPPN0">Step 2: Move your fleet to the scan location</h2><p>Once your fleet is ready, move it to the area where you want to scan.</p><p>You can use your normal fleet movement options, such as:</p><ul>
<li class="wysiwyg-list-bold" data-list-item-id="ebbcffc1c1fd42c167f7cb91cb8218df1"><strong>Warp</strong></li>
<li class="wysiwyg-list-bold" data-list-item-id="e23d46da34d306fd1aea2c9025d22614e"><strong>Subwarp</strong></li>
<li data-list-item-id="e3797174ad4474203db129557b6cf656a">
<strong>Warp Gate</strong> when available</li>
</ul><p>When your fleet arrives, keep it undocked and select it.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6YTTAPJQ536EW5A0TPPZYM">Step 3: Open the Scan menu</h2><p>To begin scanning:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="e9043b225f41d17909fa56c750c867625">Select your fleet.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e70163025faa45520c2c825ae86eee57c">Open the fleet action menu.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ee652bb26516361a5b6280641d21cce3d">Click <strong>Scan</strong>.</li>
</ol><p>This opens the <strong>Scan Sweep</strong> view.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 2241/1172;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52275776517139" width="2241" height="1172"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6YVTZV7X9NX48BK0P07AMN">Step 4: Choose a scan pattern</h2><p>In the <strong>Scan Sweep</strong> view, you will see several scan patterns.</p><p>Each pattern has its own scanning characteristics, the selected pattern affects the scan area and the cost of the scan.</p><p>For example, different patterns may change:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="e2713e33c30d19c2f25fb8b8a5993ec64">The size of the scan area</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e7407d6d08e7147ee88deaa41d2ac33d5">The signal value</li>
<li data-list-item-id="eaf36dbb4800d7ad3194e16c7aeb5274e">The amount of <strong>Repair Kits</strong> required</li>
</ul><p>To start a scan:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="e3132b6d94502f335b2a6da89a90f3e73">Review the available scan patterns.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ec109522417e246fda3ae16c43e38af77">Click the pattern you want to use.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ea13a83c960c131a50fde15724beafa50">Confirm the scan by clicking <strong>Ready</strong>.</li>
</ol><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 663/1349;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52275776517523" width="663" height="1349"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6YXW5H0MN3ZRJB6TF0P80T">Step 5: Start scanning</h2><p>After selecting a scan pattern and confirming it, your fleet will begin the scan sweep.</p><p>The goal of scanning is to find <strong>SDUs</strong>, which can later be used for crafting recipes.</p><p>Depending on future updates, scanning behavior, results, and follow-up actions may change.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT6YY58D7S4T4EQGMBJGMRP8">Summary</h2><p>To scan in C4 PTR:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="ed659d700dbb1f266ee746d2d1efa96b3">Create a fleet.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ee273f975ecaebac90deeb88e66a45823">Add <strong>Fuel</strong> and <strong>Repair Kits</strong>.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e71e0c6a33e51ce744db30ca4827015eb">Undock the fleet.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e693baa643453e7be27688d6f0ffc8cff">Move it to the area you want to scan.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ec02144214d43a9306462cd6226d49f02">Select the fleet.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e8530c8b039376e84bbb2510ec65c57f6">Click <strong>Scan</strong>.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="eeb7a841ec0255e7871b148faba95ff9e">Choose a scan pattern.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e8f932f2b34de85d3c5bfc5004a3c781a">Click <strong>Ready</strong> to begin the scan.</li>
</ol><p>Scanning is used to find <strong>SDUs</strong> for crafting, so it is an important part of the broader resource and production loop</p></div>

          

          
        </div>
      </section>

